HEADWORD: Infestive
<hw>In*fest"ive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>infestivus</ets>. See <er>In-</er> not, and
<er>Festive</er>.]</ety> <def>Having no mirth; not festive or merry;
dull; cheerless; gloomy; forlorn.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Infestivity</ent>⟦br⟧
